---

<DocsLayout
  title="DuckDB"
  description="dbt-burla with DuckDB for zero-setup local dev, CI, or self-contained demos."
  lede="You want zero-setup local development, CI integration tests, or a self-contained demo. DuckDB is embedded, ephemeral, and single-machine — perfect for everything except production pipelines."
  crumbs={[{ title: "Warehouses", href: withBase("/docs/") }]}
  toc={toc}
  prev={{ title: "Overview", href: withBase("/docs/") }}
  next={{ title: "Snowflake", href: withBase("/warehouses/snowflake/") }}
>
  <p><code>burla_duckdb</code> wraps <a href="https://github.com/duckdb/dbt-duckdb">dbt-duckdb</a> and routes Python models through Burla.</p>

  <h2 id="install">Install</h2>
  <Code code={`pip install "dbt-burla[duckdb]"`} lang="bash" theme="github-dark-dimmed" />
  <p>This pulls in <code>dbt-duckdb</code>, <code>duckdb</code>, and the Burla client.</p>

  <h2 id="profile">profiles.yml</h2>
  <p>Start from your existing <code>dbt-duckdb</code> profile and swap <code>type: duckdb</code> for <code>type: burla_duckdb</code>:</p>
  <Code code={`my_project:
  target: dev
  outputs:
    dev:
      type: burla_duckdb
      path: ./warehouse.duckdb
      schema: main
      threads: 1
      burla_default_workers: 16
      # burla_cluster_url: https://cluster.burla.dev
      # burla_fake: true           # recommended for local dev / CI`} lang="yaml" theme="github-dark-dimmed" />
  <p>Everything <code>dbt-duckdb</code> supports works: <code>path: ":memory:"</code>, <code>attach:</code>, <code>filesystems:</code>, <code>extensions:</code>, etc.</p>

  <h2 id="right-pick">When this is the right pick</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Local development</strong> — iterate on Python models without a real cluster. Set <code>burla_fake: true</code>.</li>
    <li><strong>CI</strong> — embedded, zero setup, full Python code path still runs.</li>
    <li><strong>Demos / tutorials</strong> — see the <a href={withBase("/examples/quickstart-duckdb/")}>quickstart example</a>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="not">When not to use it</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Production</strong> — DuckDB is single-machine and ephemeral. Use <code>burla_snowflake</code> or <code>burla_bigquery</code>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="caveats">Known caveats</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><code>view</code> materialization for Python is not supported (dbt-core limitation).</li>
    <li>DuckDB connections are per-thread; dbt-burla reuses the thread connection already open for SQL.</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
